UserService class provides business logic for user-related operations. This service handles user creation, retrieval, and management with event publishing for system integration.

pub struct UserService {
    user_repo: Arc<UserRepository>,
    event_bus: EventBus,
}

impl UserService {
    pub async fn create_user(&self, dto: CreateUserDto) -> Result<User> {
        let user = User::from_dto(dto)?;
        self.user_repo.save(&user).await?;
        self.event_bus.publish(UserCreated(user.id)).await;
        Ok(user)
    }
}

UserService class implementation for handling user-related business operations. This class provides methods for user retrieval with caching for improved performance.

class UserService {
    constructor(private repo: UserRepository, private cache: CacheService) {}

    async getUser(id: string): Promise<User | null> {
        const cached = await this.cache.get(`user:${id}`);
        if (cached) return cached;
        return this.repo.findById(id);
    }
}

CacheManager with distributed Redis caching and local LRU fallback. This manager provides initialization and configuration methods for setting up the caching infrastructure.

pub struct CacheManager {
    redis: RedisClient,
    local: LruCache<String, Vec<u8>>,
    ttl: Duration,
}

impl CacheManager {
    pub fn init(redis_url: &str, capacity: usize) -> Self {
        let redis = RedisClient::connect(redis_url);
        let local = LruCache::new(capacity);
        Self { redis, local, ttl: Duration::from_secs(300) }
    }
}

